subsections.text:
Prior research has confirmed the effectiveness of fitness tracking technologies in increasing users' physical activity level (e.g. [W1587923037], [W2129343065], [W2333629723], [UNMAPPED:29], [W2025454211], [W2601036553]). For example, using fitness trackers (e.g. Fitbit, pedometer) can increase the level of moderate-to-vigorous activities [W1995092424], [W2522531501], [W2009938297], [W2138694790] and goal directed activities [W1994309940], [W2113886271], [W2025454211], [W2116535495], [W2072088591]. [W2602572407] also have found that extended use of a fitness tracker – the number of features a user employs in addition to step counting (e.g. stair counting, workout tracking, goal setting, or social features) – has a positive impact on physical activity level. (See **TABLE 6**).

